      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that the same Levites",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " might ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "have the tithes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] R.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "for they, the Levites, take the tithes.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " LXX. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δεκατοῦντες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Vulg. ‘accipient decimas.’ The word in the Hebrew which generally denotes ‘to pay tithe of something,’ is here used in a special sense of collecting tithe, in which it is found in the later Hebrew of the Mishnah. It occurs here in the sense of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀποδεκατόω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 7:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ‘to take tithes of the people.’",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in all the cities of our tillage",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] LXX. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν πάσαις πόλεσιν δουλείας ἡμῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Vulg. ‘ex omnibus civitatibus operum nostrorum.’ Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 27:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘over them that did the work of the field for tillage of the ground.’ The translation of ‘",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "abodah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "’ by ‘tillage’ gives the only probable sense. The alternative, ‘cities of our service’ would be meaningless. The words are important as determining the agricultural character of the area from which this tithe was collected. It is implied, though not stated, that the tithe thus collected by the Levites was of ‘the fruits of the field’ (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 14:22-29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:12-15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and did not include the tithe of ‘the herd or the flock.’ See note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The word ‘",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Abodah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "’ was in later times technically used for ‘worship.’ Cf. the saying of Simon the Just in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Pirqe Aboth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘On three things the world is stayed; on the Thorah, and on the Worship (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Abodah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and on the bestowal of kindnesses’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
