  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 37.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The first-fruits of our dough",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 15:18-21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And our offerings",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Literally, \"our heave offerings\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 15:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 23:11, 17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "To the chambers of the house",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The store-chambers attached to the temple-building (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 13:4, 5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The tithes of our ground",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As with the law of first-fruits, so with that of tithes (which was more burthensome), there had grown up a practice of neglecting it on the part of  many, if not of all. The natural result  would be the non-attendance of Levites at  Jerusalem, and so a falling-off in the  solemnity and grandeur of the temple-worship (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 13:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It was now  covenanted afresh on the part of the people  that they would resume the legal practice,  at any rate to the extent of paying what has  been called \"the first tithe,\" or that due to  the Levites for their sustentation. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "In all  the cities of our tillage",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Levitical tithe  was not taken to Jerusalem. but stored up in  some neighbouring, generally Levitical, city. Nehemiah 10:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It was also arranged to contribute the first-fruits prescribed in the law. The infinitive להביא depends on העמדנוּ, and is co-ordinate with לתת, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The first-fruits of the ground, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 23:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 34:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; the first-fruits of all fruit trees, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 19:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; the first-born of our sons who were redeemed according to the estimation of the priest, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and of our cattle (i.e., in the case of the unclean, the required redemption, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 13:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and the firstlings of the herds and of the flocks, the fat of which was consumed on the altar, the flesh becoming the share of the priests, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the construction is altered, the first person of the imperfect taking the place of the infinitive: and we will bring the first-fruits. ערסות, probably groats or ground flour; see rem. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 15:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. תרוּמות, heave-offerings, the offering in this connection, is probably that of wheat and barley, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 45:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or of the fruits of the field, which are suitably followed by the \"fruit of all manner of trees.\" On \"the first of the wine and oil,\" comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These offerings of first-fruits were to be brought into the chambers of the house of God, where they were to be kept in store, and distributed to the priests for their support. \"And the tithes of our ground (will we bring) to the Levites; and they, the Levites, receive the tithes in all our country towns. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") And a priest, a son of Aaron, shall be with the Levites when the Levites take tithes; and the Levites shall bring the tithe of the tithes to the house of our God, into the chambers of the treasury.\" The parenthetical sentences in these verses, המעשׂרים הלויּם והם and הלויּם בּעשׂר, have been variously understood. עשׂר in the Piel and Hiphil meaning elsewhere to pay tithe, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 14:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 26:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 28:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", many expositors adhere to this meaning in these passages also, and translate ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : for they, the Levites, must give again the tenth (to the priests); and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : when the Levites give the tenth; while the lxx, Vulgate, Syriac, Rashi, Aben Ezra, Clericus, Bertheau, and others, take עשּׂר and העשׂיר in these sentences as signifying to collect tithe. We prefer the latter view, as giving a more suitable sense. For the remark that the Levites must give back the tenth (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") does not present so appropriate a motive for the demand that the tithes should be paid, as that the tithes are due to the Levites. Still less does the addition, in our agricultural towns, suit the sentence: the Levites must give back the tithe to the priests. Again, the fact that it is not said till ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that the Levites have to give the tenth of the tenth to the priests, speaks still more against this view. A priest is to be present when the Levites take the tenth, so that the share of the priests may not be lessened. On \"the tenth of the tenth,\" comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Hezekiah had provided store-chambers in the temple, in which to deposit the tithes, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 31:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]